http://virtualenvwrapper.readthedocs.org/en/latest/command_ref.html

https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Python_VirtualEnv#Virtualenvwrapper

======================================


     Create the virtualenv:

$ mkvirtualenv -p /usr/bin/python2.7 my_env


    Activate the virtualenv:

$ workon my_env


    Install some package inside the virtualenv (say, Django):

(my_env)$ pip install django


    list site packages

(my_env)$ lssitepackages

    Do your things
    ...


    Leave the virtualenv:

(my_env)$ deactivate

======================================


    list all virtualenvs

$ lsvirtualenv



    show details of a single virtualenv

$ showvirtualenv my_env



    remove an environment

$ rmvirtualenv some_env



    duplicate an env

$ cpvirtualenv env new_env



    Path management
    Adds the specified directories to the Python path for the currently-active virtualenv.

$ add2virtualenv directory1 directory2 ...
